===date:Thu Oct  2 13:35:35 2003
===more:Norman Rockwell believed that American values were universal human values. President Roosevelt was careful to associate the "Four Freedoms" with people "everywhere in the world." Did Rockwell's depiction of these freedoms in American cultural terms undermine this universal message?  Who are Rockwell's Americans who embody the "Four Freedoms"? Consider the social settings in which they were portrayed. Who got left out?  

